  Additional AI Touchpoint: The "Why" Prompt

  Trigger

  First time a seeker writes a note exceeding 550 characters AND the note contains reflective language ("because", "I realized", "I noticed", "I feel").

  What Happens

  Claude prompts: "You've been reflecting deeply. Can I ask - why is [target] important to you? What would change if you achieved it?"

  Seeker responds. Claude follows up with 1-2 deeper "why" questions.

  Output

  The seeker's "why" is captured and stored. It appears:
  - In their CPO reports (reminder of motivation)
  - When they miss targets (gentle reconnection to purpose)
  - In their Sprint dashboard (optional display)

  Why This Matters

  Most seekers track targets they think they should want, not targets they actually want. The "why" excavation helps them discover if they're chasing the
  right thing - or running from something else.

  ---
  Cost Consideration

  At scale (1,000 users, weekly reports), estimated Claude API cost: ~$2-8 per user per month depending on context size. At $100/month pricing, this is
  sustainable with healthy margin. If I move to lower price points, I'd batch reports or reduce frequency for lower tiers.

  ---
  Summary: Claude transforms SelfPM from a tracking tool into a reflection partner. The AI doesn't just store data - it helps seekers understand their
  data, which is the entire point.
